The course deals with the concept of the game and its nature; the connection of the game with different aspects of the child's development (cognitive and social development); classical and modern game theories; principles and techniques of game observation; the role of the adult in the child's game and the methods of game instruction; different types of games; the importance and criteria of the toy.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop an understanding of the nature of play and its importance in a child's development, the ability to analyze and create children's play and environment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows the theoretical bases of the game and the meaning of the game in the child's development; 2) can analyze children's play and play environment; 3) is able to supervise children's play and create a developing playing enviroment.
